YENAGOA – A police inspector, Michael Timitimi, attached to the Bayelsa State Police Command has slumped and died. The incident occurred during the burial rites of his grandmother in Igbedi community in Kolokuma/Opokuma Local Government Area. The officer’s death has thrown the security agencies, including the State Vigilante Service and Bayelsa Volunteer Service into a mournful mood. Eyewitnesses said he slumped and died shortly after dancing fitfully at the wake in honour of his grandmother. A visit to the headquarters of some security outfits showed the officers were shocked and mournful after news of the police inspector’s death was broken to them. The Chairman of Bayelsa State Volunteers, Hon. Oyinkuro Lucky Asanakpo, and the leadership of the agency have paid a condolence visit to the family of Timitimi who was formerly attached to the security outfit. (The Nation) Yenagoa - The Police in Bayelsa said on Sunday they had strengthened security in the state towards ensuring a hitch-free Dec. 5 governorship election. This is coming just as the Inspector-General of Police (IG), Solomon Arase, is scheduled to pay a visit to the state on Tuesday. The Police Public… In "News" By Nathan Nwakamma Yenagoa - The Police in Bayelsa says it is investigating the recent armed attack on Oronto Douglas’ residence and Okoroba community in Nembe Local Government Area of the state. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) recalls that Douglas was attacked by yet to be identified gunmen on… In "Metro" Abuja （Sundiata Post）- Suspected gunmen have killed the chairman, Cattle Breeders Association, Bayelsa State chapter, Alhaji Abdulkarim Jubril, and three other persons said to be his employees. It was learnt that the incident occurred on Saturday afternoon along the Bayelsa Palm Road in Yenagoa Local Government Area of the state.… In "News"